  "body": "QBFT currently sends a round change as soon as the request timeout has expired. This can result in a round change being sent on round 0 before there is a block that has been created. Without a block the network might stall if the network goes into round change.\n\nFrom the issue raised in the interop discussion channel\n> For the new height, the round change would not happen until, the block period has passed and the node has the proposal ready to propose.",
